Durban - One person was severely injured when a truck crashed into trees on the N2 south bound, just after the Higginson Highway, on Friday afternoon. The accident brought traffic to near halt, as emergency workers, battled for two hours to free a trapped passenger. The IPSS helicopter was also used in the rescue. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. SAPS Search and Rescue, the eThekwini Fire department, and paramedic teams Rescue Care and IPSS freed the passenger who was stuck in the truck. Garrith Jamieson, of Rescue Care, said: “A truck left the roadway and collided into trees at the side of the road. The truck was carrying a driver and a passenger. The passenger was severely entrapped. "The Durban fire department used the jaws of life to rescue the passenger. The driver sustained moderate injuries, and the passenger was freed after more than two hours, with severe injuries. He is being stabilised and taken to the nearest hospital.” To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
